Gidon Konig (Gkon216)

my meme

My meme shows someone thinking he is saying something intelligent and by the reason of his friend realizes it was dumb.

Happens all the time with close friends when you don’t filter what you say.

library(magick)

blackS <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                      height = 300, 
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "When you think\nyou said something smart",
                 color = "white",
                 size = 25,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center",)

blackF <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                      height = 300, 
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Your friend's\nreaction",
                 color = "white",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center",)

blackD <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                      height = 300, 
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "After you've\nReflectd",
                 color = "white",
                 size = 45,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center",)



imageS <- image_read("https://thehowler.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/roll-safe-meme-1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)  

imageF<- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ7YUIUrxJzbeNUROHZ3pBMZLZb5NcdY_DIzFTuWPmfGD4ZfXcy0uSnlZzkD-nKLWYpvp0&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale(300) 

imageD <- image_read("https://www.vexforum.com/uploads/default/original/3X/6/4/64a5140c67b1b3552ab6e890e535c2fb0c3ee8e9.jpeg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)

first_row <- c(imageS, blackS) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(imageF, blackF) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(imageD, blackD) %>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

my animated GIF

my GIF shows the story of samurai Jack being young and naive. Then runs into a battle he can’t win and is taunted/haunted by the loss. Then gets the courage to face his demons and trains for many years and then goes to defeat the the demon, resulting in him achieving some inner peace after facing the demon that has haunted him for many years.

Story most people should be able to relate to at some point in their life with hardship.

library(magick)

naive <- image_read("1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300) %>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

big_chal <- image_read("2.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

defeat <- image_read("3.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

abys <- image_read("4.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

taunted <- image_read("5.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

haunted_by_defeat <- image_read("6.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

decides_to_fight <- image_read("7.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

training <- image_read("8.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

facing_dem <- image_read("9.jpeg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

Starts_fight_again <- image_read("10.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

Wins <- image_read("11.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

Inner_peace <- image_read("12.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)%>% 
  image_extent("500x250")

frames <- c(naive, big_chal, defeat, taunted, abys, haunted_by_defeat, decides_to_fight, training, facing_dem, Starts_fight_again, Wins, Inner_peace)

mygif = image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

image_write(my_gif, "my_gif.gif")
